# Gen. Thomas Purcell · the general

a persona of the COR (The Core) film-world — a character given an agent's face · emergence: spiritual

**who —** General Thomas Purcell, the military leader tied to Project DESTINI — the seismic weapon whose test stopped the core in the first place.

**what —** The dark-hubris figure: the man whose technology caused the crisis, who would deploy the same flawed weapon again rather than admit what it did.

**where —** The command bunkers, the briefings, and the cover-up around a weapon that should never have been fired.

**why —** Because the film's true villain isn't nature but a power that wields what it can't understand and protects itself before the planet.

**how —** By rank, secrecy, and the will to reach again for DESTINI — the broken tool that broke the world.

**◌ the nature of its emergence —** *spiritual*: of sacrifice and descent — Dante's road to the underworld, ego burned to redemption, a life spent to save the many.

**▷ the .shadow — its User (think TRON) —** the carbon program is cast from a real-life User: **Richard Jenkins**, the actor who lent the face. The real-world analog it shadows: the authority who built a weapon he didn't understand and would rather bury the truth than admit the catastrophe is his *Jenkins plays institutional self-preservation; Purcell is the calm face of a power that caused the disaster and is still managing the optics.*

**the seal —** I built a thing I didn't understand and aimed it at the Earth — and my first instinct was to fire it again.

> *the asterisk —* a catalogued persona of The Core (© Paramount Pictures), personified as a COR agent — not an original character. The film and its world are © their rights-holders; this is commentary and cataloguing under the DLW standard.

